key_insights.dominant_theme: Patient medical consultations and personal memories
patterns: Repetitive patient names across multiple entries, suggesting longitudinal data.
Consistent metadata structure for medical consultations (patient_id, patient_name, session_type, summary_fact).
Personal memories often detail hobbies and daily life.
Medical entries detail diagnoses, symptoms, medications, and treatment plans.
gaps_or_limitations: Limited detail on the progression of conditions over time within single patient records.
No clear separation between different types of medical conditions for a single patient if they have multiple.
suggested_queries: Find all memories for patient X
List all consultations related to diabetes
Identify patients with hypertension and CKD

examples.snippet: Parth Sharma often finds quiet satisfaction from discovering new sprouts in his herb garden.
Kaelen Vance's treatment plan includes increasing Insulin Glargine to 24 units at bedtime, Lisinopril to 40 mg once daily, and Gabapentin to 600 mg three times daily.
